## this is my first time use github


## How to use git - my first time.

1. install git: sudo apt-get install git

2. config user& email: git config --global user.name "user_name"

			git config --global user.email "email_id"

3. Create a local repository: the folder will save home/"foldername"

			git init "folder_name"
			
		---> cd folder_name

4. Create a file
		touch file_name
	open text app --> gedit file_name
		
5. add file: git add file_name

6. Make commit messenger: git commit -m "content of the messenger"

7. Create repository on git-web --> push file to git clone:

		git clone https://github.com/policod/REPOSITORY_NAME.git
		
		git push origin master --> user & passwd


## How to modify git file:

open file in cmd:	cat file_name
open with in textapp:	gedit file_name
create folder:		mkdir folder_name
add line to file note: 	echo "content" >> file_name

## How to remove git file:

rm file_name
git status
--> notify: delete file
git add file_name
git status
--> the file deleted






